cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.LG

The paper deals with the anonymization of system logs, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves encoding and de-identification, which are techniques commonly used in data management and data structures (cs.DS). The reduction in storage space is also a concern in database systems (cs.DB). The analysis and diagnosis of system behavior is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the performance improvement achieved by the proposed method is a topic related to machine learning and data mining (cs.LG).
